
[1]aptitude

   APT'ITUDE, n. [of aptus, apt.]

   1. A natural or acquired disposition for a particular purpose, or
   tendency to a particular action or effect; as, oil has an aptitude to
   burn; men acquire an aptitude to particular vices.

   2. Fitness; suitableness.

   3. Aptness; readiness in learning; docility.
